  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1979-09-26", 
    "text": "Estate Tax Adjustment Act of 1979 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to increase the unified credits against the estate and gift taxes from $47,000 to $70,700, with increased phase-in amounts for 1979 and 1980. Increases from $175,000 to $250,000 the minimum gross estate necessary to impose on the executor of a United States citizen or resident the duty to make an estate tax return."
